http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/HRD-Minister-visits-school-at-Chandrampalem/article13999150.ece

The process of changing the face of government schools and bring them on par with corporate schools would commence with the ZPP High School at Chandrampalem in the city, Minister for HRD Ganta Srinivasa Rao said after a visit to the school on Wednesday.Pilot projectThe ZPP High School at Chandrampalem is being improved as a model school by providing it with modern amenities and attractive classrooms after taking it as a pilot project at the instructions of Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu who wanted all government schools converted into model schools, Mr. Srinivasa Rao said.The school with a strength of 2,442 students is the biggest in the State as far as enrolment is concerned.He inspected the school along with MLA Palla Srinivasa Rao and DEO M.V. Krishna Reddy. Head Master M. Raja Babu explained the works being done and the facilities created.It may be recalled that an Additional SP T.S.R. Prasad has mobilised funds and support to the school in providing amenities and part-time teachers.